    <DocumentationNarrative Id="source:cli:meta-schema:app:command:extract:narrative:example:050" DocumentationSubjectId="source:cli:meta-schema:app:command:extract">
      <Body>Purpose:
- extract a sanctioned `MetaSchema` workspace from a live SQL Server schema

Command surface:
- `meta-schema help`
- `meta-schema extract sqlserver --new-workspace &lt;path&gt; --connection-env &lt;name&gt; --system &lt;name&gt; (--schema &lt;name&gt; | --all-schemas) (--table &lt;name&gt; | --all-tables)`

Example:

`--connection-env` names the shell-visible environment variable that contains the SQL Server connection string.

```cmd
meta-schema extract sqlserver --new-workspace .\MetaSchema.Workspace --connection-env META_SQL_DEV --system MySystem --schema dbo --all-tables
```</Body>
      <BodyFormat>MarkdownSubset</BodyFormat>
      <LastReviewedImportBatchId>source:markdown:meta-bi-readme:batch:20260609202934808</LastReviewedImportBatchId>
      <Ordinal>050</Ordinal>
      <Origin>ImportedMarkdown</Origin>
      <ReviewStatus>Current</ReviewStatus>
      <Slot>Example</Slot>
      <SubjectKey>source:cli:meta-schema:app:command:extract</SubjectKey>
      <Title>Examples</Title>
    </DocumentationNarrative>
